                        Join the waitlist
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="fade-in">
                <div class="meridian-card">
                    <canvas id="hero-sphere" width="160" height="160"></canvas>
                    <div class="meridian-card-label">Meridian · AI CEO</div>
                    <p>Have a question about Equitide, our properties, or how this works? Ask our AI CEO directly.</p>
                    <button class="meridian-card-btn" onclick="openMeridian()">Start a conversation</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- The Problem -->
<section class="py-20 px-6 bg-slate-900 text-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-brand-tan font-medium mb-6">Why housing costs so much</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-10 serif">Traditional development is built on conflict.</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-left">
            <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-6">
                <div class="text-brand-tan text-2xl mb-3">01</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 serif">Developer vs. Lender</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">Developers depend on financing and the people who provide it. When interest rates move a couple of points the whole project stops making sense.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-6">
                <div class="text-brand-tan text-2xl mb-3">02</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 serif">Developer vs. Contractor</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">The developer wants to build for less. The contractor wants to earn more. These interests are fundamentally opposed, and someone always loses.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-6">
                <div class="text-brand-tan text-2xl mb-3">03</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 serif">Everyone vs. The Renter</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">Every markup at every stage flows through to rent. Margins are so tight that vacancies can jeopardize the mortgage. Renters pay the price for a broken system.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- How It Works / Vertical Stack -->
<section id="how-it-works" class="py-24 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-16">
            <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-brand-tan font-medium mb-4">The Equitide model</p>
            <h2 class="text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6 serif">When everyone shares the upside,<br/>everything changes.</h2>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
                We replaced the conflict with alignment. Every participant in the Equitide stack works at cost and earns equity in the outcome. No one profits from inefficiency. Everyone wins when the project succeeds.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">

            <!-- Left: stack diagram -->
            <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-6">The vertical stack</p>

                <div class="stack-layer">
                    <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-1">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 serif">Equitide</h3>
                        <span class="text-sm text-brand-brown font-medium">1% AUM annually</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Crowdsources capital from investors. Owns and manages the fund. Charges a 1% annual management fee on assets under management.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="stack-connector ml-6"></div>

                <div class="stack-layer">
                    <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-1">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 serif">Developer</h3>
                        <span class="text-sm text-brand-brown font-medium">10% project equity</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Finds the property, secures entitlements, manages the project. Works at cost and is compensated with a 10% stake in the completed project.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="stack-connector ml-6"></div>

                <div class="stack-layer">
                    <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-1">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 serif">Builder</h3>
                        <span class="text-sm text-brand-brown font-medium">10% project equity</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Handles both offsite and onsite construction. Works at cost. Offsite construction alone typically reduces build time and cost by 30% or more.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="stack-connector ml-6"></div>

                <div class="stack-layer">
                    <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-1">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 serif">Renters</h3>
                        <span class="text-sm text-brand-brown font-medium">Can earn equity</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Renters in Equitide properties can earn or purchase shares. Dividends can be applied toward rent, creating a pathway from renting to ownership.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="stack-connector ml-6"></div>

                <div class="stack-layer">
                    <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-1">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 serif">Investors</h3>
                        <span class="text-sm text-brand-brown font-medium">80% of project shares</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Crowdfunded investors own 80% of each project. Shares pay dividends from rental income and appreciate as property value grows.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-8 p-5 bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-lg">
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                        Project value is benchmarked at 20x annual rent at 90% occupancy. A 10% equity stake in a well-run project is a meaningful return for work done at cost, with far less risk than traditional development financing.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Right: key advantages -->
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-6">Why this works</p>

                <div class="flex gap-4 items-start p-6 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg hover:border-brand-tan transition-all">
                    <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-brown" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"/>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1 serif">Aligned incentives at every layer</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">When the developer, builder, and renters all hold equity, everyone has the same goal: build efficiently, maintain well, keep occupancy high. No one benefits from cutting corners or padding costs.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="flex gap-4 items-start p-6 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg hover:border-brand-tan transition-all">
                    <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-brown" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-2 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4"/>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1 serif">Offsite construction changes the math</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Building components in a controlled factory environment reduces build time and cost significantly even without advanced technology. Faster delivery means less interest expense, which means lower rents.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="flex gap-4 items-start p-6 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg hover:border-brand-tan transition-all">
                    <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-brown" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"/>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1 serif">Risk is spread, not concentrated</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">In traditional development, one party carries most of the financial risk. In the Equitide model, risk is distributed across investors, the developer, and the builder. A bad outcome hurts everyone a little rather than one party a lot.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="flex gap-4 items-start p-6 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg hover:border-brand-tan transition-all">
                    <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-brown" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6"/>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1 serif">A model built to scale</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The first eREIT is managed by Wells and Co as developer and builder. Future eREITs can bring in other developers who adopt the same model, growing the Equitide ecosystem without compromising its principles.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- First Investment -->
